<p>It's been the standard response that naming standards aren't that important, even when following them does not negatively affect users in any way.  I disagree--but even so, I'm not sure I understand the difficulty with the change.</p>

<p>From your checked-out copy of the framework:</p>

<h1>Rename {{Decode.php}} to {{Decoder.php}}</h1>

<h1>Run this Bash script:</h1>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
TRUNK_PATH = /path/to/Zend/trunk/
for filename in $(find $TRUNK_PATH -type f -name '*.php' | sort); do
    sed 's/Zend_Mime_Decode/&amp;r/g' $filename &gt; $filename.sed
    mv $filename.sed $filename
    echo "Modified $filename"
done
</code></pre>

